  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Since the data size is large (> 30), normality was assumed (Gravetter & Wallnau, 2011).",
    "Levene's test confirmed the homogeneity of variances across profiles with non-significant results (all p values > 0.51).",
    "Based on one-way ANOVA results, there was a significant difference in post-test scores across the different AI interaction profiles, F (4, 138) = 5.43, p <.001, with small effect size, η²= 0.14.",
    "Post-hoc comparisons using the Tukey HSD test revealed that AI-Assisted Code Refiners had significantly higher scores than AI-Reliant Code Generators (p =.047); AI-Independent Coders had significantly higher scores than AI-Reliant Code Generators (p =.003), AI-Reliant Code Generator & Refiners (p =.016) and AI-Collaborative Coders (p =.034).",
    "For the 2nd session, the Shapiro-Wilk test revealed that the AI-Assisted Code Refiners deviated significantly from normality, W (43) = 0.862, p <.001, while other profiles did not (all p values > 0.20)."
  ],
